## Task 4 HTTP(S): Accessing the Web

- Purpose: Defines browser-server communication.
- Ports: HTTP (80), HTTPS (443).
- Methods: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE.
Example:
- Browser requests page from MACHINE_IP.
- Server responds with HTML.
- Wireshark analysis: Shows client requests (red) and server responses (blue), including metadata like server version and last modified date.
- Manual testing with telnet:
- Connect to port 80.
- Send GET / HTTP/1.1 and Host: anything.
- Server responds with page.
- Can request specific files (GET /file.html).

